SELECT * 
FROM conptr_class1 T1
where T1.bldat = '$vFecha_aconsultar$' 
and (SELECT count(*) from conptr_class1 where bldat = '$vFecha_aconsultar$')>0 
and (SELECT count(*) from conptr_class2 where bldat = '$vFecha_aconsultar$')>0
and (SELECT count(*) from conptr_class3 where bldat = '$vFecha_aconsultar$')>0
union
SELECT * 
FROM conptr_class2 T2
WHERE T2.bldat = '$vFecha_aconsultar$' 
and (SELECT count(*) from conptr_class1 where bldat = '$vFecha_aconsultar$')>0 
and (SELECT count(*) from conptr_class2 where bldat = '$vFecha_aconsultar$')>0
and (SELECT count(*) from conptr_class3 where bldat = '$vFecha_aconsultar$')>0
union
SELECT * 
FROM conptr_class3 T3
WHERE T3.bldat = '$vFecha_aconsultar$' 
and (SELECT count(*) from conptr_class1 where bldat = '$vFecha_aconsultar$')>0 
and (SELECT count(*) from conptr_class2 where bldat = '$vFecha_aconsultar$')>0
and (SELECT count(*) from conptr_class3 where bldat = '$vFecha_aconsultar$')>0
;

WITH 
parte1_PS  AS  (
SELECT  count(*) 
from conptr_class1 
where  bldat = '$vFecha_aconsultar$'
 ) ,
     
parte2_SA   AS  (
 SELECT  count(*)
 from  conptr_class2  
where bldat = '$vFecha_aconsultar$'
 ) 

SELECT  * 

FROM  conptr_class1  t1

where  t1.bldat = '$vFecha_aconsultar$' 
AND 
(select  *  from  parte1_PS)  >  0 
and 
(select  *  from  parte2_SA)  >  0

union 

SELECT  *
 
FROM  conptr_class2  T2

WHERE  t2.bldat = '$vFecha_aconsultar$'
 and 
(select  *  from  parte1_PS)  > 0 
and 
(select  *  from  parte2_SA) > 0
;
